      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC768994f82a5c100582208189c241cfd2"></a>Adjusting the front fork
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e2998"> </a>The front fork can be adjusted in rebound, compression and spring preload.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3000"> </a>This adjustment is done using the outer adjusters:
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">1 </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3004"> </a>to adjust rebound damping;
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">2 </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3007"> </a>to adjust internal spring preload
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
         <div class="Trattino_outer" style="margin-left: 0pt;">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
               <tr style="vertical-align: baseline;">
                  <td>
                     <div class="Trattino_inner" style="width: 20pt; white-space: nowrap;">3 </div>
                  </td>
                  <td width="100%">
                     <div class="Trattino_inner">
                        <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3010"> </a>to adjust compression damping.
                        </div>
                     </div>
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3013"> </a>Park the motorcycle in a stable position on its side stand.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3015"> </a>Turn adjuster (1), set on the top of each fork leg, with a flat screwdriver to adjust rebound damping.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3017"> </a>Turn the adjuster (3) on the bottom of each fork leg with a flat-blade screwdriver to adjust the compression damping setting.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3019"> </a>As you turn the adjusters (1) and (3), you will hear them click. Each click corresponds to different damping setting.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3021"> </a>The stiffest damping setting is obtained with the adjuster turned fully clockwise to the “0” position.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3023"> </a>Start with this position and turn anticlockwise. Count the clicks, which correspond to position 1, 2 and so forth.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e3025"> </a>To change the preload of the spring inside each fork leg, turn the hex. adjuster (2): every full turn clockwise corresponds
            to 1 mm of spring preload, up to a maximum of 15 mm.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_4_015002870.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
